<chapter xml:id="ch_mag" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Magnetism</title>
	<introduction>
    <p> In this chapter you will learn about magnetism.</p>
	
	</introduction>
		
    <objectives>
      
      <introduction><p>After successful completion of this chapter, you will be able to:</p></introduction>
		<ol>
			<li><p>Determine the magnetic field at a given location due to a collection of line currents.</p></li>
			<li><p>Determine the magnetic force on a charged object with a given speed due to a magnetic field.</p></li>
			<li><p>Use forces and Newton's 2nd Law to describe the motion of charges subject to magnetic forces.</p></li>
			<li><p>Distinguish between the magnetic force and the magnetic field.</p></li>
			<li><p>Determine the magnetic potential energy of a magnetic dipole in a magnetic field.</p></li>
			<li><p>Determine the torque on a magnetic dipole due to a magnetic field.</p></li>
		</ol>
	</objectives>

